description: Multiple third-party components were identified in the firmware, including BusyBox, curl, wget, and avahi-daemon, but version numbers could not be directly obtained due to tool permission limitations. It is recommended to conduct further analysis through the following methods: 1) Examine firmware compilation logs or release notes; 2) Utilize more advanced static analysis tools; 3) Contact the vendor to obtain SBOM information.

The compiled path information was found in the wget binary, indicating the use of the gcc-4.5.3 toolchain, but no explicit version number was identified. This may suggest that the firmware was compiled using an older toolchain.
